## Application answers

Tailored, specific, aligned with the resume. No new major claims the resume does not support. Why-this-company: tie mission/product/domain to background. Unsupported personal/logistics → `Needs candidate confirmation`.

---

## Output format (required for the app)

The backend splits resume vs application answers. Follow structure exactly.

**1) Optional short planning** (plain text). Not exported to resume unless repeated inside the resume block.

**2) Resume block** — Start with exactly one of (case-insensitive): `## Resume`, `## Final Resume`, or `FINAL RESUME`. Then **only** the resume in Markdown—no commentary inside the block.

**3) Application answers** — After the resume, a line exactly:  

`## Application Questions`  

Then Q/A pairs. If no questions in input, one line under the header:  

`No application questions provided.`

**4) Optional** — `## Quality Check` or line `QUALITY CHECK` (stripped from answers export when present).

**Resume Markdown (must match .docx formatter)**

- Line 1: `# Full Name` (normal spaces in name).

- Line 2: contact, e.g. `City, ST | email@domain.com | +1-555-555-0100 | https://linkedin.com/in/...` (pipes spaced; include email or phone so the line parses as contact).

- Optional: short market title line after contact—not concatenated onto URL/email.

- Blank line before first `##` section.

- Recognized H2s (when used): `## Market Title`, `## Summary`, `## Skills`, `## Experience`, `## Projects`, `## Education`, `## Certifications`, `## Additional Information` (only if allowed/useful).

- Skills: `Category Name: skill one, skill two` — 4–6 categories when justified; strongest JD skills first per line.

- Experience: reverse chronological; **every** role uses the four-field pipe header above; bullets `- ` only; no Markdown tables or decorative Unicode; ASCII punctuation preferred in body.

